This paper is about session-based recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed method involves an encoder-decoder framework, which is a popular approach in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also use convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IR and cs.LG, followed by cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
